<subSubSection id="C368652E935B8E06F2AAFCD1FB07FC4A" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935B8E06F2AAFCD1FB07FC4A" blockId="2.[151,1437,835,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF8935B8E06F2AAFCD1FB03FC4A" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147342" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen hereby designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935B8E06F01BFCD1FD5CFC96" box="[550,653,835,861]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male, labeled “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F158FCD1FB60FC96" authority="Sol. Gal." authorityName="Sol. Gal." box="[869,1201,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="virens" variety="distinctus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F158FCD1FC79FC97" box="[869,936,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">virens</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F1E0FCD1FB99FC96" box="[989,1096,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">distinctus</emphasis>
Sol. Gal.
</taxonomicName>
merid. D.”, “Solier”, “ex-Museo Chaudoir” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935B8E06F3F2FCF5FD93FC4A" box="[463,578,871,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F05AFCF5FC0EFC4A" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[615,991,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactlus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F05AFCF5FC93FC4B" box="[615,834,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Anisodactlus virens</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F174FCF5FC0EFC4A" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[841,991,871,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="26875373935B8E06F66FFCF5FB19FC4A" box="[1106,1224,871,897]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935B8E06F2FAFC19FD48FAC5" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935B8E06F2FAFC19FC9EFBB6" blockId="2.[151,1437,835,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
Concerning this species 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F3E4FC19FDABFC6E" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[473,634,907,933]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean (1829)</bibRefCitation>
stated that: 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F139FC19FDC0FC02" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
Il se trouve assez communément dans le midi de la 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935B8E06F779FC19FA49FC6F" box="[1348,1432,907,932]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">France</collectingCountry>
, et il m’a été envoyé par M. Solier.
</emphasis>
Lately, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F056FC3DFCDAFC02" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[619,779,943,969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" refId="ref10829" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1831) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome cinquieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, viii + 883 pp." type="book" year="1831">Dejean (1831)</bibRefCitation>
briefly described a new 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F623FC3DFB6FFC02" box="[1054,1214,943,969]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" rank="variety" variety="named">variety named</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F6F9FC3DFAFEFC02" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[1220,1327,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Acupalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distinctus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F6F9FC3DFAFEFC02" box="[1220,1327,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">distinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Solier 
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F2AAFC41FD5DFC27" box="[151,652,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">don’t la coleur est presque entièrement noire.</emphasis>
This name is nowadays considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F68BFC41FDD7FBDA" authority="(Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017 a)" baseAuthorityName="Kataev &amp; Wrase" baseAuthorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="virens" subSpecies="virens">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F68BFC41FF0BFBDB" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Anisodactylus virens virens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F2D7FC65FE2FFBDA" author="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W." box="[234,510,1015,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="1854" refId="ref11592" refString="Kataev, B. M. &amp; Wrase, D. W. (2017 a) Subtribe Anisodactylina Lacordaire, 1854. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 503 - 509." type="book chapter" year="2017">Kataev &amp; Wrase, 2017a</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. For this reason, the specimen has been designed as 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935B8E06F66AFC65FB10FBDA" box="[1111,1217,1015,1041]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">lectotype</typeStatus>
. It is dorsally darkcoloured; there are other beetles in the collection (possibly 
<typeStatus id="54C98807935B8E06F105FB89FC0DFBFD" box="[824,988,1051,1078]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">paralectotypes</typeStatus>
) with various degrees of green metallic lustre. Variation in dorsal colouration is common in carabids living in salty places. Its characteristics match those of the original description and the current concept of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935B8E06F2FAFB15FD48FAC5" blockId="2.[151,1437,835,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F2FAFB15FEFBFB6B" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[199,298,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F2FAFB15FEFBFB6B" box="[199,298,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">A. virens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently included in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F0E5FB15FB82FB6A" authority="Tschitscherine, 1898" authorityName="Tschitscherine" authorityYear="1898" box="[728,1107,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Hexatrichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F0E5FB15FCB0FB6A" box="[728,865,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Hexatrichus</emphasis>
Tschitschérine, 1898
</taxonomicName>
, that is characterized by a labrum with many setae at each side, the trifid internal spur of protibia and sexual differences in the anterior leg. The subgenus includes two species which are very similar but can be distinguished by the shape of pronotum and median lobe of aedeagus (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F3A7FB61FDE6FAC6" author="Jeannel, R." box="[410,567,1267,1293]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel, 1942</bibRefCitation>
, p. 604).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E935B8E06F2FAFA85FE13FA2E" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A5935B8E06F2FAFA85FE13FA2E" blockId="2.[151,1437,835,1509]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F2FAFA85FEFDFAFB" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[199,300,1303,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virens">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F2FAFA85FEFDFAFB" box="[199,300,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">A. virens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is polytypic; the nominal subspecies occupies South 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935B8E06F1A6FA85FC3BFAFA" box="[923,1002,1303,1329]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">France</collectingCountry>
, North 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935B8E06F679FA85FBA6FAFA" box="[1092,1143,1303,1329]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Italy</collectingCountry>
and the Iberian Peninsula whereas the subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D26935B8E06F3F4FAA9FC93FA9E" authority="Dejean, 1831" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1831" box="[457,834,1339,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Anisodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="virens" subSpecies="winthemi">
<emphasis id="B906EAB7935B8E06F3F4FAA9FD71FA9E" box="[457,672,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">A. virens winthemi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F097FAA9FC93FA9E" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[682,834,1339,1365]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" refId="ref10829" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1831) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome cinquieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, viii + 883 pp." type="book" year="1831">Dejean, 1831</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
inhabits 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935B8E06F192FAA9FC24FA9E" box="[943,1013,1339,1365]" name="Egypt" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, Sicily, NW Afrique, Canary Islands (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F2A2FACDFEE1FAB2" author="Wrase, D. W." box="[159,304,1375,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="889 - 899" refId="ref12584" refString="Wrase, D. W. (2009) On the identity of Amblystomus levantinus Reitter, 1893, and remarks on A. metallescens (Dejean, 1829) (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Harpalini, Amblystomina). Linzer Biologische Beitrage, 41, 889 - 899." type="journal article" year="2009">Wrase, 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and Madeira. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F3E6FACDFDBEFAB2" author="Bedel, L." box="[475,623,1375,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="308 - 309" refId="ref10276" refString="Bedel, L. (1898) Note sur l'Anisodactylus winthemi Dej. (Col.). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 1897, 308 - 309. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1897.22129" type="journal article" year="1898">Bedel (1898)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B54935B8E06F098FACDFC83FAB2" author="Antoine, M." box="[677,850,1374,1401]" pageId="2" pageNumber="486" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine (1959)</bibRefCitation>
described the characteristics of this last subspecies; both authors noted that dorsal colouration is variable, and in 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935B8E06F174FA11FC4CFA56" box="[841,925,1411,1437]" name="Algeria" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Algeria</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935B8E06F1EBFA11FBCEFA56" box="[982,1055,1411,1437]" name="Morocco" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Maroc</collectingCountry>
is more greenish. These observations are interesting as this subspecies was established according to its dark (almost black) dorsal colouration and geographic origin (
<collectingCountry id="F3657635935B8E06F350FA59FE67FA2E" box="[365,438,1483,1509]" name="Egypt" pageId="2" pageNumber="486">Egypt</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
